##In the city where Fang Fang and her sister in law live in Wuhan, the opinions of eight women on their identities

WECHAT betteryourlife2013

The introduction to better your life focuses on the better you and the better world that comes with it.

As the outbreak lingers, we enter a special "International Women's Day, " as if out of touch with the Hustle and bustle of shopping, pointing to groups of shoppers to replenish their supplies, no longer excited by the prospect of a half-day vacation, and more eager to get out of the house.

Forced to part with our empty wallets, March 8th gave us the opportunity to face a holiday that had been created to fight for women's equality.

Wuhan Woman Fang Fang

From Dr. Zhang Jixian, "the first person to report the outbreak, " to Fang Fang, a writer who kept a diary of his new title, to Aunt Hankou, who had Han scold her, and sister-in-law Aoyama, who shouted "fake" to the vice premier, women are a force to be reckoned with in the new crown epidemic.

Behind the rise of some women, more women are still plagued by the gender gap.

According to the World Economic Forum's Global Gender Gap Report 2020, the global average gender gap narrowed to 68.6 percent in 2019, an improvement over the previous year, but 31.4 percent of the global gender gap still needs to be narrowed, the gender gap is particularly wide in the political and economic spheres.
China closed the gender gap by 67.6 percent, ranking 106th out of 153 countries

While there is still a long way to go for equal rights for men and women, there is no denying that in recent years, the female consciousness has been awakening, as evidenced by the global metoo movement that has spread from Hollywood. Projected on the film and television works, the living space of the female role also receives more and more attention.

Set in New York in the sixty's, the great Mrs. Maisel is a highly educated, attractive stay at home wife, Miki, who turns her life around on a talk show after her husband cheats on his secretary.

Kim Ji-young, born in 1982, is an adaptation of the novel of the same name. It tells the story of a woman named Kim Ji-young, who has experienced a series of difficulties and perplexities in her childhood, school days, professional life and marriage life, with a psychological condition of playing her part intermittently.

Going back to the gender difference itself, today we want to talk about female consciousness. We asked women of all ages and in all walks of life the same question:

What does "female" mean to you?

No matter what the answer, the question is only meant to be a question -- as if your preconceptions are not broken, as if you have not yet found your way, you must first be willing to explore and experiment, to make decisions about your own life.

Gender is not the law of judging the value of people, break through the differences, learn to love themselves, be proud of themselves, is the key.

Here's what they said:

I personally don't like to be de-tagged by any kind of "identity" . The premise of a woman is to be an independent individual. Once a woman is given the label of "daughter" , "wife" , "mother" , she easily loses herself. But I'm not saying that a woman can't be a good daughter, wife, or mother, just that these identities shouldn't be all she is. I am myself first, then the gender woman.

As a moderate feminist, I believe that women and men are the same. We should not be limited by stereotypes. For example, must women not be strong enough? There's no pressure for a woman in boxing to punch a man. Must men not be gentle and considerate? I think Wu Tsing-Fong's a lot nicer than some of the crazy girls. I want all women to have the confidence to live their true selves.


To me, being a woman is just like being a man, it's just a gender. You can't change who you are. But men and women represent different personalities, different strengths.

Women have a comparative advantage in language, adaptability is also relatively strong, occasionally delicate feelings. But at the same time may not so good physical strength, too sensitive easily tangled (as if to expose himself) . Through studying abroad, deep feeling: in Foreign Countries, women and men are not much different, not because of women have requirements or constraints. They can live freely, freely, and with respect. Sometimes women are even more STOIC and strong.

I really enjoy living my life in my own way, from a woman's perspective, with optimism, with gentleness, with openness, with love, and with courage.

First of all, the problem is that the female identity as a separate concept, then I think it is relative to the concept of male identity. This is not to put these two opposite meanings, for me, female identity is more on behalf of some of the beautiful, unique aspect of women.

In terms of gender differences, such as fertility, you can't say that this is an absolute advantage or disadvantage for women. The pain and aftereffects of childbirth can be physically damaging to women, but many women can also feel spiritually unusually fulfilled and happy. I don't really think about the pros and cons of being a man myself, but it's true that women still lack more equal opportunities in the workplace.

The first thought was that it meant that the mother. But in fact, women's lives are constantly changing, as a daughter, girlfriend, wife, I think many women have never lived for themselves.

In the new era, I feel that the identity of women has changed a lot, it means to adhere to self-confidence, strong, independent (economy + personality) .

To go back to myself, I think that in general, society is less tolerant of women than men, and women are under pressure from both family and career.

Being a woman means more work, more suffering, more misunderstanding, and more social pressure.

In the division of family roles, women pay far more than men, but the benefits are not equal. In the workplace, the most outstanding women will be called strong woman, meaning that the family is not secure, because there is no more to invest in the family. But men don't seem to be born with that burden. Men's innate desire for conquest is built on women's vulnerability, but the real world is not friendly to vulnerability. Success takes time to accumulate, but the role of women in the family, leading to the family and career difficulties.

For me, being a woman means being more sensitive to the emotions around you, being more empathetic to the world, not that men can't be, but at some point, spending more time feeling the small details.

I accept myself from the bottom of my heart, not as a woman, but as an individual. Probably from the beginning of the very serious, not admit defeat to strive for the first. When reading, the first few test are girls, when learning a car full score is also a girl, and then work, we also have a lot of enterprise promotion of girls. Seeing girls in all walks of life, unyielding to break the so-called ceiling, to compete with the world, at that time, I felt that it was good to be one of the women.

In such a Patriarchal Society, a gender inequality society, women's identity means that many times in life, in the workplace will encounter some gender discrimination and gender violence.

For me, the same is true. There is a difference between the upbringing of boys and that of girls. Boys are often encouraged to express themselves, including their anger, but girls are often encouraged to take care of other people's emotions.

Because of structural gender inequality, men are in a position of relative privilege, women are in a position of relative vulnerability, and in terms of domestic violence, women are the main victims, and of course children. In the workplace, women also encounter various types of gender discrimination, such as from the recruitment process may not because of women, then after admission there will be equal pay, workplace ceiling, retirement age discrimination, pregnancy discrimination and many other issues.

Ever since I became a feminist, I've been proud to be a woman. That pride comes from being able to see why and through my own actions to make a difference in a society that, despite all the gender inequalities, sees a lot of gender inequality.

Write at the end:

The purpose of this article is not to define or defend women, but to listen to what women really think about themselves and understand them better.

We also hope that "she" , put aside "wife" , "mother" , "daughter" and other identity, but also can not be anything, anyone bound to the wonderful.

In the final analysis, each gender is only a superposition of attributes, the most important is still as a person, as one of the things, how to achieve and create their own value, live their own life.

Finally, happy holidays to all women. And hopefully, one day, we won't need it anymore.
